<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a8a2964-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s8533"><num value="8533">§ 8533.</num><heading> Unnecessary duplication</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In meeting the requirements under this subchapter, the Under Secretary shall avoid unnecessary duplication between public and private sources of data and the corresponding expenditure of funds and employment of personnel.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a8a2965-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/115/25/tIII/s303">Pub. L. 115–25, title III, § 303</ref>, <date date="2017-04-18">Apr. 18, 2017</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/131/105">131 Stat. 105</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
